# Kinri (Symfony 7 task manager)

Learning project for Symfony + recruitment prep. Keep changes small and explain Symfony concepts.

## Stack

- Symfony 7, Doctrine ORM, PostgreSQL (Docker), Twig, Symfony Security, PHPUnit
- Bootstrap 5 CDN only (no Node/PostCSS) — planned, not fully wired yet
- AssetMapper + Stimulus (CSRF on login needs `csrf-protection` controller)

## How to work with me

- Explain **WHY** before code; pause on Symfony “magic” (autowiring, attributes, firewall)
- Compare to vanilla PHP when helpful
- Don’t over-engineer — I’m learning
- Prefer **explain-only** or minimal diffs; I type most code unless I ask to implement
- When implementing code, explain what each block does — block by block
- When we finish a roadmap item, tick its checkbox in this file (`[ ]` → `[x]`)

## Architecture (mental model)

```
Request → Firewall (security.yaml) → access_control → Controller → Repository → Doctrine → DB
Forms: TaskType + handleRequest → isValid() runs entity Assert constraints → persist/flush
```

## Progress

- [x] Task CRUD: list, detail, shared `task/form.html.twig`, delete confirm + CSRF
- [x] Entities: `Task` (title, done, assignee), `User` (email, name, password, roles)
- [x] `User` table is `"user"` in Postgres — entity has `#[ORM\Table(name: '"user"')]`
- [x] Login/logout (session cookie), no signup; `/tasks` requires `ROLE_USER`
- [x] Dev users: `alice@example.com` / `bob@example.com`, password `dev` — run `php bin/console app:hash-dev-passwords` after DB reset
- [x] Validation (entity-level): `Assert` on `Task.title`, `User.email`, `User.name`

